[7] Brazil (Sao Paulo)
Date: Thu 15 Jan 2009
Source: Globo.com [Portuguese, trans. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://g1.globo.com/Noticias/SaoPaulo/0,,MUL956510-5605,00-SECRETARIA+CONFIRMA+DOIS+CASOS+DE+DENGUE+EM+SAO+PAULO.html>


The Municipal Health Secretariat confirmed on Wednesday [14 Jan 2009]
that there were 2 cases of dengue in the capital of Sao Paulo. The
patients are residents of Sacoma in the eastern zone and Campo Limpo
in the southern zone and contracted the disease [virus infection] in
December 2008. Previously, the last case of dengue had been registered
on 12 June of the past year [2008]. In 2007, there were 2624 [dengue
cases].

According to the Secretariat of Health, the actions to combat the
vector mosquito have been intensified in these 2 regions of the city.

--
